<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idaad28511-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s7012"><num value="7012">§ 7012.</num><heading> Department of the Army: seal</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Army shall have a seal for the Department of the Army. The design of the seal must be approved by the President. Judicial notice shall be taken of the seal.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idaad28512-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/157">70A Stat. 157</ref>, § 3011; renumbered § 3012, <ref href="/us/pl/99/433/tV/s501/a/2">Pub. L. 99–433, title V, § 501(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1986-10-01">Oct. 1, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1034">100 Stat. 1034</ref>; renumbered § 7012, <ref href="/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s808/a">Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(a)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/1838">132 Stat. 1838</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
